{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/eng/backend/19-05-19/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<blockquote>\n<p>This post is a summary of Egoing's <a href=\"https://www.opentutorials.org/course/3162\">lecture</a> from 'OpenTutorials - Life Coding'.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h3 id=\"insert-statement\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#insert-statement\" aria-label=\"insert statement permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>INSERT Statement</h3>\n<p>Let's start by listing the basic commands.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">SHOW DATABASES</code>: Shows the currently existing databases</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">USE database_name</code>: Selects the database to use</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">SHOW TABLES</code>: Shows the tables within the database</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">DESC table_name</code>: Shows information about the table</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">INSERT INTO table_name ( columns ) VALUES( values )</code>: Creates table data with the specified VALUES</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 760px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5fe20c16b65dbc8b67469583f1da1f81/5205c/19-05-19-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 38.94736842105263%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/5fe20c16b65dbc8b67469583f1da1f81/15813/19-05-19-1.webp 190w,\n/static/5fe20c16b65dbc8b67469583f1da1f81/1cdb2/19-05-19-1.webp 380w,\n/static/5fe20c16b65dbc8b67469583f1da1f81/9046c/19-05-19-1.webp 760w,\n/static/5fe20c16b65dbc8b67469583f1da1f81/184c4/19-05-19-1.webp 833w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/5fe20c16b65dbc8b67469583f1da1f81/a2d4f/19-05-19-1.png 190w,\n/static/5fe20c16b65dbc8b67469583f1da1f81/3f520/19-05-19-1.png 380w,\n/static/5fe20c16b65dbc8b67469583f1da1f81/3c051/19-05-19-1.png 760w,\n/static/5fe20c16b65dbc8b67469583f1da1f81/5205c/19-05-19-1.png 833w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/5fe20c16b65dbc8b67469583f1da1f81/3c051/19-05-19-1.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"select-statement\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#select-statement\" aria-label=\"select statement permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>SELECT Statement</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>MySQL official manual: <a href=\"https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/select.html\">https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/select.html</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The SELECT statement is used when reading data.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">SELECT desired_columns FROM table_name</code>: Outputs desired data from the table</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">SELECT * FROM table_name</code>: Outputs all data from the table</li>\n</ul>\n<p>From here on, I'll omit <code class=\"language-text\">SELECT desired_columns FROM table_name</code>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">~ WHERE column_name='desired_data'</code>: Outputs data containing 'desired_data'</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">~ ORDER BY column_name DESC</code>: Outputs data in descending order by 'column_name'</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">~ ORDER BY column_name DESC LIMIT number</code>: Outputs data in descending order by 'column_name', up to 'number' entries.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 701px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/aee8f3a840df0da97cfcef53b7a6cddc/49217/19-05-19-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 18.947368421052634%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAAECAYAAACOXx+WAAAACXBIWXMAAA7DAAAOwwHHb6hkAAAAgUlEQVR42mWPWw6EIAwAAVGEYOR5/6PWTBOybvyYlFKYtua+b+m9S85Z5pxCfp6neO8/7Psux3FoXDjnxBjzA0EpRWmtSa1VUkp6pgHyEIJCjfvruvQ9Q2zb9i+kMMbQKYnIkHDmMw1hSYhADT7CGKMAIjqyhrVWWY9WvmDNd/4WPs9xV6yjiwJaAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/aee8f3a840df0da97cfcef53b7a6cddc/15813/19-05-19-2.webp 190w,\n/static/aee8f3a840df0da97cfcef53b7a6cddc/1cdb2/19-05-19-2.webp 380w,\n/static/aee8f3a840df0da97cfcef53b7a6cddc/e2a71/19-05-19-2.webp 701w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 701px) 100vw, 701px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/aee8f3a840df0da97cfcef53b7a6cddc/a2d4f/19-05-19-2.png 190w,\n/static/aee8f3a840df0da97cfcef53b7a6cddc/3f520/19-05-19-2.png 380w,\n/static/aee8f3a840df0da97cfcef53b7a6cddc/49217/19-05-19-2.png 701w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 701px) 100vw, 701px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/aee8f3a840df0da97cfcef53b7a6cddc/49217/19-05-19-2.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"update-statement\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#update-statement\" aria-label=\"update statement permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>UPDATE Statement</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>MySQL official manual: <a href=\"https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/update.html\">https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/update.html</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Let's learn about the UPDATE statement for modifying data.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">UPDATE table_name SET column_name='new_content' WHERE id=number;</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>This command modifies the content of a selected column within a table, but only for the data with the id value you specify. Be careful — if you don't include 'WHERE id=number', all data will be modified, which could be a catastrophe!</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 614px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/84e7ecfd2d6dee7e277239b5c6966f30/e9131/19-05-19-3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52.63157894736842%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/84e7ecfd2d6dee7e277239b5c6966f30/15813/19-05-19-3.webp 190w,\n/static/84e7ecfd2d6dee7e277239b5c6966f30/1cdb2/19-05-19-3.webp 380w,\n/static/84e7ecfd2d6dee7e277239b5c6966f30/5316f/19-05-19-3.webp 614w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 614px) 100vw, 614px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/84e7ecfd2d6dee7e277239b5c6966f30/a2d4f/19-05-19-3.png 190w,\n/static/84e7ecfd2d6dee7e277239b5c6966f30/3f520/19-05-19-3.png 380w,\n/static/84e7ecfd2d6dee7e277239b5c6966f30/e9131/19-05-19-3.png 614w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 614px) 100vw, 614px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/84e7ecfd2d6dee7e277239b5c6966f30/e9131/19-05-19-3.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"delete-statement\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#delete-statement\" aria-label=\"delete statement permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>DELETE Statement</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>MySQL official manual: <a href=\"https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/delete.html\">https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/delete.html</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Let's learn about the DELETE statement for removing data.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">DELETE FROM table_name WHERE id=number;</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>This command deletes the data with the specified id value from the table. Again, be careful — if you don't include 'WHERE id=number', all data will be deleted, which could also be a catastrophe.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 608px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ece77bca19e6a38710e98ceb95e4fa8b/18872/19-05-19-4.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 35.26315789473684%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/ece77bca19e6a38710e98ceb95e4fa8b/15813/19-05-19-4.webp 190w,\n/static/ece77bca19e6a38710e98ceb95e4fa8b/1cdb2/19-05-19-4.webp 380w,\n/static/ece77bca19e6a38710e98ceb95e4fa8b/f5a85/19-05-19-4.webp 608w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/ece77bca19e6a38710e98ceb95e4fa8b/a2d4f/19-05-19-4.png 190w,\n/static/ece77bca19e6a38710e98ceb95e4fa8b/3f520/19-05-19-4.png 380w,\n/static/ece77bca19e6a38710e98ceb95e4fa8b/18872/19-05-19-4.png 608w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/ece77bca19e6a38710e98ceb95e4fa8b/18872/19-05-19-4.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"splitting-tables\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#splitting-tables\" aria-label=\"splitting tables permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Splitting Tables</h3>\n<p>Let's learn how to split tables to manage duplicate parts more efficiently. For example, if you want to split the table based on the author column, first create a separate table for authors.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 354px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3c1673a4e5ea48a4494deef8e959a279/8f50f/19-05-19-5.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 37.89473684210527%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/3c1673a4e5ea48a4494deef8e959a279/15813/19-05-19-5.webp 190w,\n/static/3c1673a4e5ea48a4494deef8e959a279/7d039/19-05-19-5.webp 354w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 354px) 100vw, 354px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/3c1673a4e5ea48a4494deef8e959a279/a2d4f/19-05-19-5.png 190w,\n/static/3c1673a4e5ea48a4494deef8e959a279/8f50f/19-05-19-5.png 354w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 354px) 100vw, 354px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/3c1673a4e5ea48a4494deef8e959a279/8f50f/19-05-19-5.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Then create the main table, and replace the author column with an author_id column.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 594px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/76874b978238129b07bc61ba25e26eaa/5fd3e/19-05-19-6.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 31.05263157894737%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/76874b978238129b07bc61ba25e26eaa/15813/19-05-19-6.webp 190w,\n/static/76874b978238129b07bc61ba25e26eaa/1cdb2/19-05-19-6.webp 380w,\n/static/76874b978238129b07bc61ba25e26eaa/bc223/19-05-19-6.webp 594w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 594px) 100vw, 594px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/76874b978238129b07bc61ba25e26eaa/a2d4f/19-05-19-6.png 190w,\n/static/76874b978238129b07bc61ba25e26eaa/3f520/19-05-19-6.png 380w,\n/static/76874b978238129b07bc61ba25e26eaa/5fd3e/19-05-19-6.png 594w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 594px) 100vw, 594px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/76874b978238129b07bc61ba25e26eaa/5fd3e/19-05-19-6.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"joining-tables-join\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#joining-tables-join\" aria-label=\"joining tables join permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Joining Tables (JOIN)</h3>\n<p>Let's learn how to combine the two tables we split above so we can view them together. Here we need to use the JOIN command, which is considered the core of relational databases.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 760px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f1d891bf0feb2d67e2df6727cbe68950/9b379/19-05-19-7.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 19.473684210526315%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/f1d891bf0feb2d67e2df6727cbe68950/15813/19-05-19-7.webp 190w,\n/static/f1d891bf0feb2d67e2df6727cbe68950/1cdb2/19-05-19-7.webp 380w,\n/static/f1d891bf0feb2d67e2df6727cbe68950/9046c/19-05-19-7.webp 760w,\n/static/f1d891bf0feb2d67e2df6727cbe68950/d9249/19-05-19-7.webp 951w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/f1d891bf0feb2d67e2df6727cbe68950/a2d4f/19-05-19-7.png 190w,\n/static/f1d891bf0feb2d67e2df6727cbe68950/3f520/19-05-19-7.png 380w,\n/static/f1d891bf0feb2d67e2df6727cbe68950/3c051/19-05-19-7.png 760w,\n/static/f1d891bf0feb2d67e2df6727cbe68950/9b379/19-05-19-7.png 951w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/f1d891bf0feb2d67e2df6727cbe68950/3c051/19-05-19-7.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Using the command <code class=\"language-text\">SELECT * FROM 'table1' LEFT JOIN 'table2' ON 'criterion1' = 'criterion2';</code>, you can merge 'table1' and 'table2' by matching entries where 'criterion1' equals 'criterion2'.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 760px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/46f267c1a967dfa1f7cf9640c55f5c37/e1031/19-05-19-8.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 25.789473684210527%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/46f267c1a967dfa1f7cf9640c55f5c37/15813/19-05-19-8.webp 190w,\n/static/46f267c1a967dfa1f7cf9640c55f5c37/1cdb2/19-05-19-8.webp 380w,\n/static/46f267c1a967dfa1f7cf9640c55f5c37/9046c/19-05-19-8.webp 760w,\n/static/46f267c1a967dfa1f7cf9640c55f5c37/76c9f/19-05-19-8.webp 803w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/46f267c1a967dfa1f7cf9640c55f5c37/a2d4f/19-05-19-8.png 190w,\n/static/46f267c1a967dfa1f7cf9640c55f5c37/3f520/19-05-19-8.png 380w,\n/static/46f267c1a967dfa1f7cf9640c55f5c37/3c051/19-05-19-8.png 760w,\n/static/46f267c1a967dfa1f7cf9640c55f5c37/e1031/19-05-19-8.png 803w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/46f267c1a967dfa1f7cf9640c55f5c37/3c051/19-05-19-8.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Also, if you specify only the columns you want after SELECT instead of '*', you can output a cleaner merged table.</p>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#insert-statement\">INSERT Statement</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#select-statement\">SELECT Statement</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#update-statement\">UPDATE Statement</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#delete-statement\">DELETE Statement</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#splitting-tables\">Splitting Tables</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#joining-tables-join\">Joining Tables (JOIN)</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"path":"/backend/19-05-19/","title":"MySQL CRUD and JOIN","category":"BackEnd","date":"2019-05-19"}}},"pageContext":{"postPath":"/backend/19-05-19/","language":"eng","langRegex":"/contents/eng/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2145088972","256249292","63159454"],"slicesMap":{}}